source_code:
Achterop de foto de tekst:

Belgian Premier here, enroute to Congo.

New York City - Hubert Pierlot, Prime Minister of the Belgian Government in
exile, who has just arrived here enroute to the Belgian Congo, is shown at a
press conference at the St. Regis Hotel. The 59- year-old official, who had
denounced King Leopold's capitulation to the Nazis on May 28, 1940, showed a
reconciled attitude toward the monarch, who, he said, was unable to fulfil his
functions while a prisoner.

(FS) 7-8-42 aje HYT-NY-OUT

13961 11.55A (40)
